One hundred applicants have filed in their CV’s for the vacant Lesotho job following the departure of South African coach, Thabo Senong, in late 2021. Lesotho Football Association Spokesperson, Mikia Ntanda, told Africanfootball that three high-profile Zambian coaches have also expressed their interest in the job. They include Honour Janza who was the last Zambian coach to take Chipolopolo to the AFCON in 2015 in Equatorial Guinea where Chipolopolo made a group stage exit with two draws and a defeat. Wedson Nyirenda, who was Zambia coach from 2016 to 2018, and guided Chipolopolo to the 2018 CHAN quarterfinals in Morocco, has also expressed interest in the job. Ex-Zambia U20 and U17 coach Osward Mutapa who was also former Chipolopolo coach Milutin Sredojevic assistant is also on the list of candidates. Mutapa won both the COSAFA U20 and U17 Championships in 2019. --AfricanFootball-- 